		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=37328' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;"><span style='color:#336600;'>Kousotsu</span></a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									Journeyman
								<br>
									Posts: 47<br>
													Registered: 05-24-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=37328'>			
	
			<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/troll.jpg" border=0 alt="">
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								Server: Druzzil Ro<br>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 290 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_5.gif' border=0 alt='3 ratings - 5.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Bards have the unique ability to create multiple effects at once.&nbsp;By weaving different songs together, a bard can customize effects to any situation.&nbsp; This makes nimble fingers and quick thinking a must for those who want to play a bard.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is a total misconception others have about bards.&nbsp; A cleric can cast multiple buffs, as can shaman, druid, etc.&nbsp; Having multiple songs up makes me unique only in the sense that no other class has the same songs.&nbsp; Nothing about this has to necessitate&nbsp;quick thinking, other than which songs I would choose to have up.&nbsp; It only is&nbsp;a must&nbsp;to have nimble fingers because my songs last a scant 18 seconds, while other class's buffs can last upwards of 3 hours.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Such ablilties as heal, mana regeneration, find corpse, accelerated travel and group invisibility make a bard invaluable group members.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>None of this applies any more except maybe mana regeneration, which is also marginalized by the abundance of other mana regen effects and buffs.&nbsp; My regen is pathetic now for as hard as mobs hit.&nbsp; Given a regen of 80 per tick, I can regen up to 800 a minute, in the same time, I will have taken nearly 10 thousand damage.&nbsp; My group invisibility song is so short that I cannot even cover members in auto-follow, with full extended range aa's, unless I follow them, which means that I then have to give explicit directions for how to get places as I cannot lead.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>If you are a social person who likes meeting new people, the bard may be for you.&nbsp; If you like to go off on your own a lot or are shy about travelling with strangers, you may want to think twice about playing a bard.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is a joke.&nbsp; It should be the other way around, by far.&nbsp; It should say, if you like to meet new people, play an enchanter, or a wizard, or cleric (etc.).&nbsp; If you like to feel like you're stuck in your own little world with no possible release or ability to talk to others while playing a game designed to be social, a bard is definitely for you.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I once saw a pretty well reasoned argument on a message board that the most powerful group you could put together would be 6 bards.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This I have really no idea about, but I can make a guess as to how the group would be set up.&nbsp; 1 bard is CoM/Mastruq/Echo, 1 bard for 5chants/slow (also would be tank), then 4 bards chain screaming(?)...There really isn't much potential at this point for a 6 bard group.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think the bard class needs to be redefined, or if not redefined, at least give us options for what we are able to do.&nbsp; For instance, if I had a healing focus effect that was on a different song than echo of the trusik, I might feel inclined to make a choice between songs.&nbsp; That's something I don't have to do anymore, because there are only a few songs worth playing together at the same time at my level.&nbsp; Give me choices for what role I am able to fill in groups, instead of being confined to overhaste/manaregen, no matter what group I am in, unless it's a kite group.&nbsp; We are supposed to be diverse by nature, so I don't feel selfish in asking for something like this for bards.&nbsp; The most diversity I have at the moment is whether my raid wants me to overhaste the rogues or provide overnuke power for the wizards, both of which are the same song.</DIV></DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
		<tr>

						<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			<span class=date_text>07-29-2004</span> <span class=time_text>11:30 AM</span>
			</span>
			</td>

						
			
