						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Here is my first attempt at a definition of The Everquest Bard:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bards&nbsp;are the Swiss Army Knives of EQ.&nbsp; While they are surpassed in specific roles by more specialized classes, their huge range of abilities allows them to adapt to different situations and different group needs rapidly and smoothly.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Though they cannot fill a primary role in a group such as healing, tanking, or dealing direct damage as well as the other, more specialized classes, Bards are never a redundant addition to a group.&nbsp; Their unique musical talents allow them to add power to their group above and beyond what a group without any music can do.&nbsp; They have a lot of utility abilities often needed for specific situations and encounters.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The bard by himself is cunning killer.&nbsp; Lacking the offensive and defensive power of the warrior, bards must rely on their music to decieve, confuse, intimidate, distract, and impede their enemies.&nbsp; With time, an experienced bard can often slaughter his enemies by the power of his music alone.&nbsp; This is not to say that his fighting abilities should be ignored, however.&nbsp; While bards lack the great offensive and defensive strength of other melee and hybrid classes, their fighting abilities are considerable, and the bards of Norrath are as familiar with their weapons as they are with their instruments.</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Impressario Feroce of <br>Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild on<br>Firiona Vie
							</div>
																
										</td></tr>
