						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Definition of bard from EQ developers:&nbsp; A class we put into the game so we could nerf them over and over again and put in useless aa's to force them to achieve less than a quarter of the power of any other class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Definition of bard from people who play:&nbsp; I can AE kite and have alot of AA's but I still cant do much of anything!&nbsp; Who cares if i ruined this class for the rest of you, I got what I want and carpal to boot!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Definition of a bard from a raid's perspective:&nbsp; We have 2 Macro'd bards already, why do we need anymore?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only thing a bard is good at is kiting mobs and PC's if you play on a pvp server.&nbsp; Everything else is done and done better by other classes.&nbsp; Also another role bards take is the guilt trip role&nbsp;for taking certain gear because in the long run other classes can use it more efficiently than a bard.&nbsp; I am so sick of people telling me I shouldnt have item A through Z cuz it benefits casters or hybrids or warriors or priests alot more.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So you might ask why I play a bard?&nbsp; Because most everything we do is manaless and I do not have to worry about not using my songs&nbsp;ever.&nbsp; Sitting around for 3 to 4 minutes so I can once again re-use my spells drives me nuts.</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
